Package io.sphere.sdk.models

Provides the common API types of SPHERE.IO.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Builder<T>
    A Builder is a mutable data container to create an immutable instance of another type.
    CreationTimestamped  
    DefaultModel<T>
    A default model is a real resource in SPHERE.IO which can be referenced and always consists of the fields id, version, createdAt, lastModifiedAt.
    DefaultModelView<T>
    A default model view is a view for a resource in SPHERE.IO always consists of the fields id, version, createdAt, lastModifiedAt.
    ErrorResponse  
    Identifiable<T>
    Something that is identifiable via an ID.
    Image  
    MetaAttributes  
    MetaAttributesDsl  
    Referenceable<T>
    Represents an object itself or a Reference to it.
    SphereEnumeration  
    Timestamped  
    Versioned<T>
    Something that has an ID and a version.
    WithKey  
    WithLocalizedSlug
